OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F318A1777558268
OL,3,CTrump says King 'agrees with me' that
OL,4,CIran should never have nuclear weapon
OL,6,FCharles's most diplomatically
OL,7,Fsensitive state visit to date comes
OL,8,Famid a backdrop of a barrage of
OL,9,Fcriticism levelled by Mr Trump at
OL,10,FPrime Minister Sir Keir Starmer over
OL,11,Fthe war in Iran.
OL,13,FThe president has accused the UK of
OL,14,Fhaving a "terrible" approach to the
OL,15,Fconflict.
OL,17,FThe King meanwhile called on Mr Trump
OL,18,Fto "renew" the bonds of friendship
OL,19,Fbetween America and the UK at this
OL,20,F"critical time".
OL,26,@vD@JOUvD@SO]zD@DOUzD@JO]|D@AOU|D@OO]
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G3/14
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,319,300,200,140,000,100
PN,31804
SC,0004
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F318A1777558268
OL,3,CTrump says King 'agrees with me' that
OL,4,CIran should never have nuclear weapon
OL,6,FCharles, in a shorter, less formal and
OL,7,Fmore personal speech than his historic
OL,8,Faddress to Congress, told the American
OL,9,Fleader it was "an important
OL,10,Fopportunity" and that the two nations
OL,11,Fhave stood together in "the best of
OL,12,Ftimes and worst of times".
OL,14,FIn his toast at the grand White House
OL,15,Fstate dinner, the King said the
OL,16,F"indispensable alliance" was a
OL,17,F"cornerstone of prosperity and
OL,18,Fsecurity for both British and American
OL,19,Fcitizens".
OL,26,@qD@OOUrD@LO]sD@XOUtD@YO]xD@AOUxD@XO]yD@
OL,26,AAOU{D@IO]
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G4/14
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,319,300,200,140,000,100
PN,31805
SC,0005
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F318A1777558268
OL,3,CTrump says King 'agrees with me' that
OL,4,CIran should never have nuclear weapon
OL,6,FIn his own toast, Mr Trump
OL,7,Fcongratulated the King on his
OL,8,Ffantastic speech to Congress, saying:
OL,9,F"He got the Democrats to stand. I've
OL,10,Fnever been able to do that."
OL,12,FMr Trump said, despite America's
OL,13,Findependence in 1776, the relationship
OL,14,Fbetween the UK and the US was
OL,15,F"unbreakable in any conflict" and had
OL,16,Fgrown into "a friendship unlike any
OL,17,Fother on earth, a very, very special
OL,18,Fand incredible friendship".
OL,26,@qD@AOUrD@\O]wD@AOUwD@]O]xD@LOUzD@ZO]
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G5/14
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,319,300,200,140,000,100
PN,31806
SC,0006
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F318A1777558268
OL,3,CTrump says King 'agrees with me' that
OL,4,CIran should never have nuclear weapon
OL,6,FThe monarch, whose state visit comes
OL,7,Famid both the Iran war and conflict in
OL,8,FUkraine, made reference to "those who
OL,9,Fwish us harm across the world", adding
OL,10,Fin his toast on Tuesday evening:
OL,11,F"Those challenges encourage us to
OL,12,Freaffirm, tonight, the basis on which
OL,13,Four partnership has been built".
OL,15,FAnd in a personal gift to Mr Trump,
OL,16,Fthe King presented the president with
OL,17,Fthe original bell from the Royal Navy
OL,18,FSecond World War submarine HMS Trump,
OL,19,Fquipping: "If you should ever need to
OL,20,Fget hold of us... well just give us a
OL,21,Fring."
OL,26,@pD@\OUqD@^O]sD@AOUuD@_O]{D@KOU}D@FO]
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G6/14
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,319,300,200,140,000,100
PN,31807
SC,0007
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F318A1777558268
OL,3,CTrump says King 'agrees with me' that
OL,4,CIran should never have nuclear weapon
OL,6,FThe King reflected on the challenging
OL,7,Frelationship between the UK and the US
OL,8,Fin the past, saying: "Yes, we have had
OL,9,Four moments of difficulty even in more
OL,10,Frecent history.
OL,12,F"When my mother visited in 1957, not
OL,13,Fthe least of her tasks was to help put
OL,14,Fthe 'special' back into our
OL,15,Frelationship after a crisis in the
OL,16,FMiddle East.
OL,18,F"Nearly 70 years on, it is hard to
OL,19,Fimagine anything like that happening
OL,20,Ftoday..."
OL,26,@pD@VOUtD@AOUzD@AOU|D@IO]
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G7/14
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,319,300,200,140,000,100
PN,31808
SC,0008
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F318A1777558268
OL,3,CTrump says King 'agrees with me' that
OL,4,CIran should never have nuclear weapon
OL,6,FCharles added: "I am so glad we have
OL,7,Fan important opportunity, at this
OL,8,Fcritical time, to renew those bonds of
OL,9,Fhistory and friendship between our
OL,10,Fnations and our peoples."
OL,12,FHe told the guests: "Tonight, we are
OL,13,Fhere to renew an indispensable
OL,14,Falliance which has long been a
OL,15,Fcornerstone of prosperity and security
OL,16,Ffor both British and American citizens.
OL,18,F"Our people have fought and fallen
OL,19,Ftogether in defence of the values we
OL,20,Fcherish.
OL,26,@nD@POUrD@YO]tD@UOUzD@AOU
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G8/14
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,319,300,200,140,000,100
PN,31809
SC,0009
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F318A1777558268
OL,3,CTrump says King 'agrees with me' that
OL,4,CIran should never have nuclear weapon
OL,6,F"Across the ocean, and from coast to
OL,7,Fcoast, we have traded, innovated and
OL,8,Fcreated together. We have stood
OL,9,Ftogether through the best and worst of
OL,10,Ftimes."
OL,12,FIn a lighter moment, the King remarked
OL,13,Fhow Mr Trump has said how if it were
OL,14,Fnot for the US, European countries
OL,15,Fwould be speaking German, and he joked
OL,16,Fin return: "Dare I say that, if it
OL,17,Fwasn't for us, you'd be speaking
OL,18,FFrench!"
OL,26,@nD@AOUrD@GO]xD@LOUzD@HO]
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G9/14
