CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F318A1777558268
OL,3,CTrump says King 'agrees with me' that
OL,4,CIran should never have nuclear weapon
OL,6,FThe first lady was in charge of the
OL,7,Fpreparations for the dinner, where the
OL,8,FKing and Queen were feted with a menu
OL,9,Fof Garden vegetable veloute, spring
OL,10,Fherbed ravioli, dover sole, and a
OL,11,Fbeehive-shaped flourless chocolate
OL,12,Fgateau, after a busy day of
OL,13,Fengagements in Washington DC.
OL,15,FMr Trump's ease with the King was on
OL,16,Fshow, with the president pictured
OL,17,Fsmiling and touching a grinning
OL,18,FCharles's knee as they sat side by
OL,19,Fside in chairs during a bilateral
OL,20,Fmeeting in the Oval Office.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                   G13/14
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
